    dc:creator "BAMBER, ROGER N" ;
    dc:date "2013" ;
    dc:title "A re-assessment of Konarus Bamber, 2006 and sympatric leptocheliids from Australasia, and of Pseudoleptochelia Lang, 1973 (Crustacea: Peracarida: Tanaidacea)" ;
    bibo:endPage "39" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2013-08-01" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "3694" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098898>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098916>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098918>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098920>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098922> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098898>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Konarus straddi comb. nov., A, female, dorsal, with A′, detail of carapace margin; B, antennule; C, antenna; D, labrum; E, left mandible; F, right mandible; G, labium; H, maxillule; I, maxilliped; J, epignath. Scale line = 1.0 mm for A, 0.2 mm for B to J." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10098898/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098916>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Pseudoleptochelia anomala, female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, antennule; C, antenna; D, labrum; E, right mandible; F, left mandible; G, labium; H, maxillule; I, maxilliped and endite; J, epignath. Scale line = 1.0 mm for A, 0.2 mm for B to J." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10098916/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098918>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Pseudoleptochelia anomala, female. A, left cheliped; B, same, inner face of chela; C to F, pereopods 1 to 4; G, pereopod 6; H. pleopod (most setae represented by their bases only); I, uropod of neuter; J, uropod of brooding female. Scale line = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10098918/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098920>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Pseudoleptochelia anomala, male. A, habitus, dorsal; B, antennule (most aesthetascs represented by their bases only); C, antenna; D, pleopod (most setae represented by their bases only); E, uropod of 1.6 mm male; F, right and G, left uropods (ventral) of 1.8 mm male. Scale line = 0.8 mm for A, 0.2 mm for B to G." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10098920/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098922>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Pseudoleptochelia anomala, male. A, right cheliped; B to G, pereopods 1 to 6 respectively. Scale line = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10098922/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

